Process called "is_tuple_type" that takes obj as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if object is a tuple type using pure Runa reflection
    Try:
        Note: Use reflection runtime call for type information
        Let type_info be system_call_reflection_get_type_info with obj as obj
        If type_info is not None and type_info contains key "name":
            Let type_name be type_info at key "name"
            Return type_name is equal to "Tuple"
        Otherwise:
            Return false
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "get_object_metadata" that takes obj as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get metadata dictionary for an object using pure Runa reflection
    Try:
        Note: Use reflection runtime call for object metadata
        Let type_info be system_call_reflection_get_type_info with obj as obj
        If type_info is not None and type_info contains key "metadata":
            Return type_info at key "metadata"
        Otherwise:
            Note: Fallback: create basic metadata
            Let type_name be get_type_name with obj as obj
            Return dictionary containing:
                "type" as type_name
                "module" as get_module_name with obj as obj
                "object_id" as get_object_id with obj as obj
    Catch error:
        Note: Ultimate fallback: return empty metadata
        Return dictionary containing

Process called "integer_to_hex_string" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert integer to hexadecimal string
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    
    Let hex_digits be "0123456789abcdef"
    Let result be ""
    Let abs_value be absolute_value with value as value
    
    While abs_value is greater than 0:
        Let digit_index be abs_value modulo 16
        Let hex_char be character_at with string as hex_digits and index as digit_index
        Set result to hex_char plus result
        Set abs_value to abs_value divided by 16
    
    If value is less than 0:
        Set result to "-" plus result
    
    Return result

Process called "compute_object_hash" that takes obj as Any returns Integer:
    Note: Compute hash value for object
    Try:
        Return system_call_compute_object_hash with obj as obj
    Catch error:
        Note: Simple fallback hash based on string representation
        Let str_repr be string_representation with obj as obj
        Return simple_string_hash with string as str_repr

Process called "estimate_primitive_size" that takes obj as Any returns Integer:
    Note: Estimate size of primitive type
    Let type_name be get_type_name with obj as obj
    Match type_name:
        When "Boolean":
            Return 1
        When "Integer":
            Return 8
        When "Float":
            Return 8
        When "String":
            Let str_repr be string_representation with obj as obj
            Return length of str_repr
        Otherwise:
            Return 8

Process called "estimate_collection_size" that takes obj as Any returns Integer:
    Note: Estimate size of collection type
    Let base_size be 32  Note: Base overhead for collection
    Try:
        If is_list_type with obj as obj:
            Let list_length be system_call_get_list_length with obj as obj
            Return base_size plus (list_length multiplied by 8)
        If is_dictionary_type with obj as obj:
            Let dict_size be system_call_get_dictionary_size with obj as obj
            Return base_size plus (dict_size multiplied by 16)
        Return base_size
    Catch error:
        Return base_size

Process called "is_all_uppercase" that takes name as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if name is all uppercase (constant convention)
    If length of name is equal to 0:
        Return false
    
    For i from 0 to length of name minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with string as name and index as i
        If is_lowercase_letter with char as char:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "create_attribute_info" that takes name as String and value as Any and type_obj as Any returns AttributeInfo:
    Note: Create AttributeInfo structure
    Return AttributeInfo with:
        name as name
        type as get_type_name with obj as value
        value as value
        is_public as is_public_name with name as name
        is_readonly as is_readonly_attribute with obj as type_obj and name as name
        is_static as is_static_attribute with obj as type_obj and name as name
        documentation as get_attribute_documentation with obj as type_obj and name as name

Process called "create_method_info" that takes name as String and func as Any returns MethodInfo:
    Note: Create MethodInfo structure
    Return MethodInfo with:
        name as name
        function as func
        is_async as is_async_function with func as func
        is_static as is_static_method with obj as func
        parameter_names as get_parameter_names with func as func
        parameter_types as get_parameter_types with func as func
        return_type as get_return_type with func as func
        documentation as get_doc_string with obj as func
        file_path as get_function_file with func as func
        line_number as get_function_line with func as func

Process called "extract_function_signature" that takes func as Any returns Optional[FunctionSignature]:
    Note: Extract function signature from function object
    Try:
        Let signature be FunctionSignature with:
            parameter_names as get_parameter_names with func as func
            parameter_types as get_parameter_types with func as func
            return_type as get_return_type with func as func
            has_varargs as has_varargs_parameter with func as func
            has_kwargs as has_kwargs_parameter with func as func
            default_values as get_default_values with func as func
        Return Some with value as signature
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "character_at" that takes string as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Get character at specific index
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length of string:
        Return ""
    Try:
        Return system_call_character_at with string as string and index as index
    Catch error:
        Return ""

Process called "trim_whitespace" that takes string as String returns String:
    Note: Remove leading and trailing whitespace
    Let start_index be 0
    Let end_index be length of string
    
    While start_index is less than end_index:
        Let char be character_at with string as string and index as start_index
        If not is_whitespace_char with char as char:
            Break
        Set start_index to start_index plus 1
    
    While end_index is greater than start_index:
        Let char be character_at with string as string and index as (end_index minus 1)
        If not is_whitespace_char with char as char:
            Break
        Set end_index to end_index minus 1
    
    If start_index is greater than or equal to end_index:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be ""
    For i from start_index to end_index minus 1:
        Set result to result plus character_at with string as string and index as i
    Return result

Process called "contains_substring" that takes string as String and substring as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if string contains substring
    Let string_length be length of string
    Let substring_length be length of substring
    
    If substring_length is greater than string_length:
        Return false
    If substring_length is equal to 0:
        Return true
    
    For i from 0 to string_length minus substring_length:
        Let match be true
        For j from 0 to substring_length minus 1:
            If character_at with string as string and index as (i plus j) is not equal to character_at with string as substring and index as j:
                Set match to false
                Break
        If match:
            Return true
    
    Return false

Process called "count_leading_spaces" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Count leading spaces/tabs for indentation
    Let count be 0
    For i from 0 to length of string minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with string as string and index as i
        If char is equal to " ":
            Set count to count plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\t":
            Set count to count plus 4  Note: Tab counts as 4 spaces
        Otherwise:
            Break
    Return count

Process called "string_representation" that takes obj as Any returns String:
    Note: Get string representation of object
    Try:
        Return system_call_object_to_string with obj as obj
    Catch error:
        Return "<object>"

Process called "contains_digit" that takes string as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if string contains any digit
    For i from 0 to length of string minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with string as string and index as i
        If is_digit_char with char as char:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "simple_string_hash" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Simple hash function for strings
    Let hash_value be 0
    Let prime be 31
    
    For i from 0 to length of string minus 1:
        Let char be character_at with string as string and index as i
        Let char_code be character_to_ascii with char as char
        Set hash_value to hash_value multiplied by prime plus char_code
    
    Return hash_value

Process called "is_lowercase_letter" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is lowercase letter
    If length of char is not equal to 1:
        Return false
    Let ascii_code be character_to_ascii with char as char
    Return ascii_code is greater than or equal to 97 and ascii_code is less than or equal to 122

Process called "is_whitespace_char" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is whitespace
    If length of char is not equal to 1:
        Return false
    Let ascii_code be character_to_ascii with char as char
    Return ascii_code is equal to 32 or ascii_code is equal to 9 or ascii_code is equal to 10 or ascii_code is equal to 13

Process called "is_digit_char" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is digit
    If length of char is not equal to 1:
        Return false
    Let ascii_code be character_to_ascii with char as char
    Return ascii_code is greater than or equal to 48 and ascii_code is less than or equal to 57

Process called "character_to_ascii" that takes char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Convert character to ASCII code
    Try:
        Return system_call_character_to_ascii with char as char
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "absolute_value" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return absolute value of integer
    If value is less than 0:
        Return negative value
    Otherwise:
        Return value 